        conseils: "Peille is an authentic and untouristy village: that is its strength. Wear good shoes for the steep cobbled lanes. The village can be explored in 1 to 1.5 hours. Ask to see the 'Moulin à huile' (old olive press) and the medieval fortified gate. The village's single restaurant offers family-style Nice cuisine with valley views: book ahead as there are only about fifteen seats. The panorama from the orientation table (above the church) is extraordinary: on clear days, you can see Corsica. For hikers, the trail to Mont Baudon (1,264 m) starts from the village: allow 3 hours return. Ideal to visit in spring or autumn for the colours and mild temperatures.",
