        description: "Taxi transfer from Nice to the Garavan quarter in Menton, featuring the Cocteau Museum, exceptional gardens and citrus heritage.",
        routeDescription: "33 km — approximately 40 minutes via the A8 or Moyenne Corniche",
        introduction: "Menton-Garavan refers to the eastern quarter of Menton, closest to the Italian border, a peaceful haven home to some of the Côte d'Azur's most precious cultural and botanical treasures. It is here, in the Old Port bastion, that the Jean Cocteau Museum — Séverin Wunderman Collection houses the world's largest collection of the multi-talented artist's work: drawings, ceramics, tapestries and films. The Wedding Hall of the Town Hall, entirely decorated by Cocteau in 1957, is a masterpiece in itself. But Garavan is above all famous for its exceptional gardens, the legacy of 19th-century British winter visitors who took advantage of France's mildest microclimate to acclimatise tropical plants. The Serre de la Madone Garden, created by Lawrence Johnston (also creator of Hidcote Manor in England), is a terraced botanical garden cascading down the hillside with rare plant collections from around the world. The Val Rahmeh Exotic Botanical Garden harbours subtropical species unique in continental Europe. Every February-March, the Lemon Festival transforms Menton into a dazzling spectacle with citrus-decorated floats and illuminated gardens. The Garavan quarter, with its Belle Époque villas hidden in lush vegetation, stepped alleys and sea views, is a world apart on the Riviera.",
        itineraire: "From Nice, two routes are available. Via the A8 motorway, head towards Italy and take exit 59 Menton. Drive down to Garavan via Avenue de Sospel then Avenue Katherine Mansfield. The journey takes 35-40 minutes. The scenic alternative follows the Middle Corniche (D6007) through Villefranche-sur-Mer and Èze, offering spectacular views, then descends to Menton via Cap Martin. For the Serre de la Madone Garden, ask the driver to drop you at 74 Route du Val de Gorbio (accessed from the Gorbio road). For the Cocteau Museum, head to the Bastion on the Old Port on Quai Napoléon III. The Garavan quarter is residential and quiet with narrow streets, but our driver knows the most practical access routes.",
        conseils: "The Lemon Festival (February-March) is the major event: book your taxi well in advance as the whole town celebrates and traffic is diverted. The Serre de la Madone Garden is open Tuesday to Sunday — visit in the morning for the best light and fewer crowds. Easily combined in a day with the Cocteau Museum and Menton's covered market. Old Menton with its Saint Michael Basilica is a 15-minute walk from Garavan. For lunch, Old Port restaurants offer delicious Franco-Italian cuisine. In summer, Garavan beach is less crowded than central Menton beaches. The quarter is also the starting point of the coastal path to Italy, a beautiful cliff-side walk.",
