        conseils: "The Alpha Wolf Park is the star attraction: the 'scénovisions' (night-time shows in summer where wolves howl in the forest) are an unforgettable experience — book absolutely. Allow 2 to 3 hours for the park visit. For hikers, the Boréon valley offers trails for all levels: the Lac du Boréon walk (easy, 1 hour) is perfect for families, while the Fenestre Lakes or Pas des Ladres are more challenging day hikes. In summer, the Boréon water is refreshingly cool for swimming. The village of Saint-Martin deserves at least a 1-hour stroll to admire the arcaded houses and taste local specialities: Swiss chard pie, ravioli with daube sauce, ganses pastries. In winter, La Colmiane resort (15 km before Saint-Martin) offers affordable family skiing. Note: after Storm Alex (2020), some road sections were rebuilt — the road is passable but works may cause delays.",
