        conseils: "The stop at the Saut des Français is essential: ask the driver to pull over at the belvedere to admire the vertiginous view over the Vésubie gorges, 300 metres below. The main square of Levens, with its plane trees and cafés, is one of the most pleasant spots in the hinterland for a drink or terrace lunch. The village hosts several traditional festivals: the Olive Festival in November and a renowned Christmas market. Marshal Masséna's birthplace can be visited by appointment. For hikers, the Tour de Levens trail (2h30, easy) circles the plateau with views of the Mercantour and the sea. Local gastronomy highlights Levens olive oil and mountain produce: pies, ravioli and fougassettes. Levens can be combined with Tourrette-Levens or Duranus for a hinterland village circuit.",
