        conseils: "The ideal season to visit Contes is autumn: the chestnut trees turn flamboyant colours in October-November, and the Chestnut Festival (usually the third Sunday of November) brings the village alive with roasted chestnuts, chestnut cakes and new wine. The olive oil mill can be visited during pressing season (November to February): you can watch the olives being crushed and buy freshly pressed oil, an exceptional product. The baroque church deserves a visit for its trompe-l'oeil decorations. For hikers, the trail from Contes to Châteauneuf-Villevieille (1h30 one way, easy) offers panoramic views over the entire Paillon valley and coast. Village restaurants serve homely Niçois cuisine: pissaladière, Swiss chard pie, stockfish. Contes can be combined with Peillon (10 km) or Lucéram (15 km) for a day discovering the Nice hinterland.",
