        conseils: "The old village of Gattières deserves a quiet hour's stroll to appreciate its lanes, ancient doors and viewpoints. The belvedere near the castle ruins offers the best panoramic view over the Var valley — an ideal photography spot, especially in the morning when the light illuminates the mountains. The ridge trail (1h30, easy) above the village is an ideal walk to enjoy the panorama without excessive effort. The Sunday morning market, small but authentic, offers local products: olives, cheeses, local vegetables. Le Belvédère restaurant, on the main square, serves honest Provençal cuisine with a panoramic terrace. Gattières combines naturally with Carros (5 km), Le Broc or Vence for a circuit of Nice's western villages. In the evening, the village is a romantic spot to watch the sunset over the valley.",
