        conseils: "The Butterfly Museum, in the Lascaris Castle, is the must-see visit: allow 45 minutes to an hour to admire the collection of 5,000 specimens. It is an ideal family visit that fascinates children and adults alike. The castle itself offers a fine viewpoint from its terrace. The prehistoric caves below the village are accessible by guided tour — enquire at the town hall or Nice tourist office for times. The old village can be pleasantly explored in 30 minutes, with its shaded lanes and stone houses. The restaurant La Table de Tourette, on the village square, offers careful Provençal cuisine with a panoramic terrace. Tourette-Levens combines easily with Falicon (5 km) or Levens (13 km) for a circuit of Nice's eastern perched villages. The hiking trails around the village (notably towards Mont Macaron, 804 m) offer 2 to 3-hour walks with magnificent views.",
