        conseils: "Wear good walking shoes for the climb to the citadel: the path is cobbled and fairly steep in places, but the view from the top is extraordinary. The climb takes 20 minutes and the citadel visit about 45 minutes. Citadel entry is charged (about €5). For a perfect day, combine the outbound taxi with a Train des Pignes return: the train from Entrevaux to Nice takes about 1h45 and crosses scenery inaccessible by road. The village can be explored in 2-3 hours including the citadel. Restaurants within the walled town are few but charming: try traditional Provençal cooking at one of the two inns on the main street. Market day is Friday morning inside the town. In summer, baroque music concerts are sometimes held in the cathedral, taking advantage of the exceptional acoustics of the historic organ. Entrevaux can be combined with Puget-Théniers (13 km) for a day discovering the Var valley.",
