        description: "Taxi transfer from Nice to Tende, a mountain village in the upper Roya valley, gateway to the legendary Valley of Wonders and its Bronze Age rock engravings.",
        routeDescription: "80 km — approximately 1h30 via the A8 then D6204 (Roya valley)",
        introduction: "Tende is a fascinating mountain village perched at 815 metres altitude in the upper Roya valley, on the edge of the Alpes-Maritimes department and just a few kilometres from the Italian border. This commune of 2,000 inhabitants is best known as the gateway to the Valley of Wonders, a unique archaeological site in Europe containing over 40,000 Bronze Age rock engravings, classified as a Historic Monument. The departmental Museum of Wonders, housed in the heart of the village, displays casts and discoveries from this exceptional site. Tende itself is well worth a visit: its tall houses of green schist with stone slab roofs are stacked on a rocky spur, overlooked by the ruins of the Lascaris castle. The collegiate church of Notre-Dame de l'Assomption, with its sculpted green schist Renaissance portal, is a gem of Alpine religious art. The journey from Nice follows the entire Roya valley, through spectacular gorges carved in limestone, passing through Breil-sur-Roya and Saorge, one of the most beautiful perched villages in France. Tende is also the starting point for the Col de Tende and the road tunnel to Cuneo in Italy, the historic route linking Piedmont to the Mediterranean.",
        itineraire: "From Nice, take the A8 motorway towards Italy as far as Ventimiglia, then take the exit for Breil-sur-Roya and the Roya valley via the D6204. This road follows the entire valley along the tumultuous course of the Roya, first passing through the narrow gorges of Saorge with their tunnels carved into the rock. You'll pass through Breil-sur-Roya, then Saorge, a spectacular village clinging to the cliff in an amphitheatre, before continuing to Fontan and Saint-Dalmas-de-Tende. The arrival in Tende is from the south, with a striking view of the tall schist houses stacked on the rocky spur. The alternative route via Sospel and the Col de Brouis is shorter in distance but more winding and slower. Your driver will choose the best route according to the day's conditions.",
        conseils: "The Nice–Tende journey is long and the Roya road is winding: settle in comfortably and enjoy the magnificent scenery. If your goal is the Valley of Wonders, note that the site is only accessible on foot between June and October (snow blocks the trails the rest of the year). Guided tours depart from the Refuge des Merveilles or the Lac des Mesches, accessible by 4x4 from Tende — your driver can arrange the transfer. The Museum of Wonders is open all year (except Tuesday) and is an excellent off-season alternative. In Tende, try the local mountain cuisine: borage ravioli, potato pie, sheep's cheese. The village experiences harsh winters with frequent snow from December to March. In summer, Tende is a cool haven at 815 m altitude when heatwaves hit the coast.",
